    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-01-07T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-01-07T17:00:00-05:00" n="42"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d42">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">701.4511/1–746: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Commissioner in India</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Merrell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-01-07T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 7, 1946—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>18. For your information, Brit Govt through BritEmb here has asked Dept to
                    reconsider question of raising status of Indian Agent General<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d42fn2">Sir Girja Shankar Bajpai.</note> to that of fully accredited
                    Minister. It is understood Chinese Govt has agreed to raise status of Indian
                    representative in China and of Chinese representative in India.</p>
                <p>Dept has informed BritEmb that, for reasons previously given (Dept’s 869 Nov.
                        7<note n="3" xml:id="d42fn3">See <ref target="frus1945v06#pg_263">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1945, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">vi</hi>, p. 263</ref>, footnote 44.</note>), it
                    prefers to postpone making any decision in this matter.</p>
                <p>Repeated to London and Chungking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
